## ðŸ› Bug Report

The current type definition for the validator compiler is missing the function type return type.

```ts
export interface FastifyValidationResult {
  errors?: FastifySchemaValidationError[] | null;
}

export type FastifySchemaCompiler = (routeSchema: FastifyRouteSchemaDef) => FastifyValidationResult
```

It should look more like this to reflect the current JavaScript code:

```ts
export interface FastifyValidatorFunction {
  (data: any): { error?: Error | null, value?: any } | false;
  errors?: FastifySchemaValidationError[] | null;
}

export type FastifySchemaCompiler = (routeSchema: FastifyRouteSchemaDef) => FastifyValidatorFunction
```

Also I'm not sure why the `errors` field exists on the validator function.

## To Reproduce

Steps to reproduce the behavior:

```js
server.post("/test", {
  validatorCompiler: ({ schema }) => {
    return data => {
      if (!data || data.constructor != Object) {
        return { error: new Error("value is not an object") }
      }
      return { value: data }
    }
  }
}, async req => req.body)
```

Resulting type error:

```
Type '({ schema }: FastifyRouteSchemaDef) => (data: any) => { error: Error; value?: undefined; } | { value: any; error?: undefined; }' is not assignable to type 'FastifySchemaCompiler'.
  Type '(data: any) => { error: Error; value?: undefined; } | { value: any; error?: undefined; }' has no properties in common with type 'FastifyValidationResult'.
```

## Your Environment

- *node version*: 14
- *fastify version*: 3.10.1
- *os*: Linux
